With your hands deep in the man's trouser pockets, you discover that he does not in fact have a wallet, which is peculiar given that he also isn't dead. Your eyes meet.\n\n"Please get out of my pockets and leave me be," he says, "and maybe have a little think about what it is you really want from life".\n\nYou go back indoors and drink some fruit squash. His words will haunt you for the rest of your days.\n<h1>YOU LOSE</h1>\n<<remember $scum = "y">>
You leave the supermarket carrying an item that you have not paid for. The RFID scanners go off. Everybody looks at you in speechless shock as a security guard tackles you to the ground, breaking one of your ribs in the process. The bone will eventually heal, but you will forever be known among the people of this town as "that pikey kid who tried to shoplift a pizza".\n<h1>YOU LOSE</h1>\n<<remember $thief = "y">>
You decide to eat the pizza standing in the supermarket without paying for it. No sooner than your teeth touch molten cheese are they dashed from your face by the fist of the burliest, most overzealous security guard you have ever seen. <<if visited("pubguy3")>>\s\nThere are screams and strange fleshy noises coming from inside the bank. You had better leave the situation be.\n<<else>>\s\nThis is the bank. It is not a very important place to you really. If pressed, you would probably describe it as "banky", or "just sort of like a normal bank". <<if $metpubguy is "y">><<set $scoutedbank = "y">>You recall the nasty man from behind the pub and his apparent predilection for robbing such establishments. You make a mental note of the bank's lack of security features, and an electronic sign proudly declaring the bank's "11 days since last robbery".<<endif>>\n<<endif>>\s\n\n[[Back to the town square|town]]

You remember that you are not allowed in the pub. You were barred last week for calling one of the beloved regulars a "bell-end". Such vulgar language, honestly. Simply despicable. He wasn't hurting anyone.\n\nThere might be something of interest [[round the back of the pub|roundback]], or you can go [[back to the town square|town]].
You fancy some of that crappy supermarket own-brand pizza. Look, there's some right there in the "hot" food section. Go on, [[grab it|getpizza]].\n\n[[Leave|town]]
This is your kitchen. It can be described as such since it possesses all the necessary qualities of kitchenhood, but in no way is this a comfortable place to be. You suspect it is haunted.\n\n<<if $clothes is "naked">>\s\n<b>You are naked</b>. Perhaps for now you can [[fashion the curtains into some makeshift garb|kitchen][$clothes = "curtain"]].\n\n<<endif>>\s\nYou can get to your [[bedroom]] from here, or go <<if $clothes is "naked">>[[outside|lawndeath]].You probably shouldn't go outside in your curent state of undress, but whatever, you're the boss.<<else>>[[outside|lawn]].<<endif>>
Idiot. The terrifying voice could not have been more clear.\n\nYou experience great pain and die horribly.\n<h1>YOU LOSE</h1>\n<<remember $moron = "y">>
<<set $havepizza = "y">>\s\nAww yeah, pizza! [[Eat that shit!|eatpizza]]\n\n[[Leave|town]]
Oh god, you did it. You really did it. It's all gone. Shit.\n\n[[Back to Achievements|Achievements]]\n<<forget $hero>><<forget $sentimental>><<forget $martyr>><<forget $thief>><<forget $glutton>><<forget $moron>><<forget $twat>><<forget $idiot>><<forget $badinfluence>><<forget $scum>><<forget $jobseeker>><<forget $pervert>><<forget $wanker>><<forget $win>>
You fancy yourself quite the Dirty Harry type, huh. Rest assured you look like an idiot with that thing. You're holding it all wrong. You're probably wondering if it even works.\n\nWell, it does. A little bit. You shoot once and the rustly mechanism grinds awkwardly and clogs itself up. There are a few high-pitched "ping!" sounds as the single bullet ricochets about the cave, before it finds home with a soft fleshy "thud". This is closely followed by a child-like squeal.\n\n[[Investigate|cave3]]
You stagger blindly in what you reckon was the general direction of the squeal. Some gravel gives way beneath your feet and you stumble. You are teetering over. You think for a split second that you have found stable footing on a rock, but it gives way under your weight and you tumble groundwards. Hmm, thinks your bumped head; giving way beneath your weight is not a thing that rocks normally tend to do.\n\nYou get your mobile phone (that you had all along) from your pocket and use the backlight to [[investigate further|cave4]].\n\n
<<set $haspyjamas = "y">>\s\nOh god oh god oh god.\n\nSo the good news is that you found the wizard, and he still has your pyjamas. In fact he is wearing them. Weird.\n\nThe bad news is that, instead of a normal humanoid head where his head should be, there is a large pool of blood and bits of brain in a directed spatter. Presumably the bullet did enough damage to render the skull structurally unstable without totally destroying it, but then you stood on it and squished the all the insides out. Well, this certainly is a new low for you. Great job, really great job.\n\nWell, at least you got your pyjamas back. Better [[skedaddle|town]].
On your way to the kitchen, a wizard appears and steals your pyjamas. Before you can protest, he vanishes.\n\nYou wonder if that was a real wizard. You decide on balance that yes, you suppose it probably was.\n\nAnyhow, you are naked and ashamed. It is best that you conceal your nether-regions somehow. Back in the [[bedroom]] is where you keep your clothes.\n\nOr perhaps, come to think of it, you're perfectly comfortable walking around your house with no clothes on? You still fancy a snack, and the food is in the [[kitchen]].
You wake up in your bed. It is 11.30am. You hate your life and everyone in it.\n\nIt suddenly occurs to you that today will be just as awful as every other day and there is no point in trying.\n\nYou [[go back to sleep|intro]].

This is the main road running through your hometown. This is not a particularly "happening" place to live; read "main road" as you would "tallest dwarf". There is no nightlife to speak of, or really even a daylife for that matter. The sky somehow manages to be overcast one hundred percent of the time, even in mid-August. The few people that inhabit this place are incredibly, deeply unpleasant. They sneer as you walk past.\n\nIt is, frankly, shit.\n\nYou want to move out as soon as you've got your shit together, but who knows how long that will take, especially given your unique propensity for incompetence.\n\nAnyhow, [[on we go|town]].\n\n

"I told you, I'm having an existential crisis. I got drunk last night and now the severity of the hangover is forcing me to contemplate the very futility of existence. We live, we die. We live only to die. Dying is the inevitable result of living. How utterly pointless. The irony."\n\nIt occurs to you that it is not particularly ironic.\n\n"Anyhow, is there anything else I can help you with?"\n\n[["You can get the hell off my lawn."|Man5]]\n\n<<if $knowname is "n">>\s\n[["What's your name?"|Ben1]]\n\n<<endif>>\s\n[["Would you like some pizza?"|Ben3]]\n\n[["Oh my god. <<set $Bengone = "y">>\s\n<<if $knowname is "y">>Ben's<<else>>The man's<<endif>> eyes open wide and his nostrils flare deeply as he sniffs the pizza you are waving at him. He noiselessly rises to accept your gift. His body language seems to be that of a subservient animal, begging for your permission; you nod sagely. He cannot believe his luck.\n\n<<if $knowname is "y">>Ben<<else>>The man<<endif>> takes the pizza and scampers away down the road. Thank fuck for that.\n\n[[Continue|lawn]]
"I simply wandered here in a state of violent inebriation. I vaguely recall this bit of lawn looking rather inviting - it appealed to my acute sense of needing a lie down. It is, I confess, actually rather bumpy and uneven. I think there might be something buried under the topsoil here. But, alas, my predicament renders me unable and unwilling to relocate. Is there anything else I can help you with?"\n\n[["You can get the hell off my lawn."|Man5]]\n\n<<if $knowname is "n">>\s\n[["What's your name?"|Ben1]]\n\n<<endif>>\s\n[["What are you doing on my lawn?|Ben2]]\n\n[["Would you like some pizza?"|Ben3]]\n\n[["Oh my god. You cannot see far into the cave because it is dark, as caves are wont to be. A terrifying voice bellows from the gloom: "<b>LEAVE THIS PLACE OR DIE HORRIBLY</b>." I suggest you [[do so|town]].<<if $havegun is "n">> Or you could ignore the voice and [[wander further into the cave|cavedeath]], what do I care?<<else>>\n\nAlthough come to think of it, you <i>do</i> have a gun. If you feel unthreatened by the prospect of committing culpable homicide, you could [[shoot wildly into the darkness|cave2]].\n<<endif>>
